### ─── SHOPPING CART (Redis-backed) ──────────────────────────

### 20. Get cart (empty initially)
### File: src/GroceryShop.Api/Controllers/CartController.cs
### Flow: CartController.GetCart()
###   → reads X-Session-Id header → CartService.GetCartAsync(sessionId)
###   → Redis GET "cart:{sessionId}" → deserialize JSON
###   → If empty → returns CartDto with zeros
### DB: Redis (not PostgreSQL)
GET http://localhost:8020/api/v1/cart
X-Session-Id: test-session-roger

###

### 21. Add item to cart
### Flow: CartService.AddItemAsync()
###   → Redis GET → deserialize → add/increment → Redis SET (24h TTL)
###   → BuildCartDtoAsync(): fetch Product from PostgreSQL
###   → Calculate: lineTotal, subTotal, tax (7%), deliveryFee ($0 if >$35, else $5.99)
### Copy a real product ID from response #5
POST http://localhost:8020/api/v1/cart/items
Content-Type: application/json
X-Session-Id: test-session-roger

{
    "productId": "PASTE_PRODUCT_ID_HERE",
    "quantity": 3
}

###

### 22. Update item quantity
PUT http://localhost:8020/api/v1/cart/items/PASTE_PRODUCT_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
X-Session-Id: test-session-roger

{
    "quantity": 1
}

###

### 23. Remove item from cart
DELETE http://localhost:8020/api/v1/cart/items/PASTE_PRODUCT_ID_HERE
X-Session-Id: test-session-roger

###

### 24. Clear entire cart
### Flow: Redis DELETE "cart:{sessionId}"
DELETE http://localhost:8020/api/v1/cart
X-Session-Id: test-session-roger


### ─── ORDERS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 25. Get Roger's orders
### File: src/GroceryShop.Api/Controllers/OrdersController.cs
### Flow: OrdersController.GetAll()
###   → reads X-User-Id header → OrderService.GetOrdersAsync(userId, page, pageSize)
###   → .Where(o => o.UserId == userId).OrderByDescending(o => o.CreatedAt)
### Copy Roger's user ID from the database query we ran earlier
GET http://localhost:8020/api/v1/orders
X-User-Id: dcfad6ae-634c-4449-95ff-985da7b71844

###

### 26. Create order from cart
### Flow: OrderService.CreateOrderAsync()
###   → CartService.GetCartAsync(sessionId) — reads from Redis
###   → If cart empty → throws InvalidOperationException
###   → Generates order number: "ORD-{date}-{4-char-guid}"
###   → Sets EstimatedDelivery = now + 45 minutes
###   → _db.Orders.Add(order) + SaveChangesAsync() — writes PostgreSQL
###   → CartService.ClearCartAsync(sessionId) — deletes Redis key
###   ⚠️ NO TRANSACTION: crash between save and clear = double order risk
### IMPORTANT: Add items to cart first (request #21), then run this
POST http://localhost:8020/api/v1/orders
Content-Type: application/json
X-Session-Id: test-session-roger
X-User-Id: dcfad6ae-634c-4449-95ff-985da7b71844

{
    "storeId": "PASTE_STORE_ID_HERE",
    "deliveryAddress": "3501 S Florida Ave, Lakeland FL 33803",
    "notes": "Ring doorbell please"
}

###

### 27. Update order status (copy order ID from response #26)
PATCH http://localhost:8020/api/v1/orders/PASTE_ORDER_ID_HERE/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": 1
}


### ─── AI CHATBOT ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 28. Chat: product search (full RAG pipeline)
### File: ai-service/app/routers/chat.py → chat_message()
### Flow:
###   1. check_custom_scenario() → None (not a special case)
###   2. get_or_create_session(null) → Redis SET "chat:{uuid}", TTL 2hr
###   3. get_history(session_id) → Redis GET → empty (first msg)
###   4. classify_intent("organic fruit") → "product_search"
###   5. get_embedding(query) → Ollama POST /api/embeddings → 768-dim vector
###   6. retrieve_products(query, top_k=10) → Qdrant.search("grocery_products")
###      detect_category_filter("organic fruit") → "Fresh" → metadata filter
###   7. retrieve_deals(query, top_k=3) → Qdrant.search("grocery_deals")
###   8. build_context(products, deals, stores) → text block
###   9. build_messages(query, context, history) → [system, user]
###  10. generate(query, context, history) → Ollama/Azure LLM → response
###  11. append_message(session_id, "user", query) → Redis
###  12. append_message(session_id, "assistant", response) → Redis
###  13. persist_message(...) → PostgreSQL ChatMessages + ChatSessions
###      Includes: LatencyMs, Model, RetrievedProductIds
### Exception: ExceptionHandlerMiddleware catches unhandled → 500 JSON
POST http://localhost:8021/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "message": "What organic fruit do you have under 5 dollars?",
    "session_id": null
}

###

### 29. Chat: follow-up (uses session for continuity)
### Copy session_id from response #28 and paste below
### Flow: same as above but step 3 returns previous messages from Redis
###   → history is injected into LLM prompt for context continuity
